  "prompt": "In IIT Bombay medical studies are there or not?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, **IIT Bombay does not offer medical studies or medical degree programs**. The Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs), including IIT Bombay, are primarily focused on engineering, technology, sciences, and related disciplines. They offer undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral programs in fields such as:\n\n- **Engineering Disciplines:** Computer Science, Electrical, Mechanical, Civil, Chemical, and more.\n- **Sciences:** Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, and interdisciplinary areas.\n- **Humanities and Social Sciences:** Management, Design, and other interdisciplinary studies.\n\nIf you're interested in pursuing medical studies in India, you might consider institutions specifically dedicated to medical education, such as:\n\n- **All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS)**\n- **Christian Medical College (CMC) Vellore**\n- **Armed Forces Medical College (AFMC)**\n- **Various state and private medical colleges** offering MBBS and other medical degrees.\n\nThese institutions are specialized in medical education and provide comprehensive training for careers in medicine, surgery, and allied health sciences.\n\nIf you have any more questions or need information on specific programs or institutions, feel free to ask!",
